Dear Clark,

Thanks for your mail - it is good to know that somebody reads this!

I am currently at a conference which doesn't have any computing
facilities apart from web browsing, so I can't edit any files, look up
any references, etc. What I put up was taken from a notebook I kept when
I was an undergraduate (a very long time ago!). I cannot now remember
where I took it from. Wherever it was, it had a brief account of the
speech, which apparently went on for many hours, but I think this was
the only bit that was quoted. It is entirely possible that either I or
the author of the unknown book made various errors in the quote itself
or the attribution, who knows?

When I get back to London I will have a shot at finding the notebook and
looking for clues about where it may have come from.

Peter.

